Discover the Island

Why We Love Aruba

Aruba — “One Happy Island” — is a stunning Caribbean paradise just off the coast of Venezuela. With year-round sunshine, turquoise waters, white-sand beaches, and a warm island culture, it’s the place our family keeps coming back to.

```
☀️
Sunshine Guaranteed
Aruba sits outside the hurricane belt with an average temperature of 82°F year-round and over 300 sunny days.
🏖️
World-Class Beaches
Eagle Beach is consistently ranked among the top beaches in the world, with powdery white sand and calm turquoise waters.
🍞
Incredible Cuisine
A delicious fusion of Caribbean, Dutch, and Latin American flavors — from fresh seafood to local favorites like keshi yena.
🤿
Underwater Wonders
Crystal-clear waters perfect for snorkeling and diving, with colorful coral reefs, shipwrecks, and vibrant marine life.

Learn More About Aruba

🌴 Aruba.com — Official Site 🗺️ VisitAruba.com — Travel Guide ⭐ TripAdvisor — Reviews & Tips 📊 Aruba Tourism Authority
```

Our Journey

A Decade of Island Memories

From our very first trip to our most recent, every visit to Aruba has woven new memories into our family story.

```
2012
Where It All Began

Our first family adventure to Aruba — discovering the magic of One Happy Island. The turquoise waters, the warm breezes, and the instant feeling of belonging. This trip started a tradition that would last over a decade.

2015
Coming Back for More

Three years later, the island called us back. By now we had our favorite beaches, our go-to restaurants, and a rhythm for the perfect island day — sand between our toes and salt on our skin.

2017
November Escape

A fall getaway to Aruba — trading chilly November weather back home for warm Caribbean sunshine. Family time on the beach, exploring the island, and making memories that kept us warm all winter long.

2022
The Reunion

After a few years away, we finally made it back to our island home. The joy of returning to familiar shores, revisiting favorite spots, and discovering new ones — Aruba never disappoints.

2024
Our Latest Chapter

Our most recent visit — and the tradition is stronger than ever. Six trips and counting. New adventures, the same incredible island spirit, and a whole new collection of family memories to cherish.

```
×

What We Love to Do

Our Favorite Island Activities

Every trip is a mix of relaxation and adventure. Here are the things that keep us coming back to Aruba year after year.

```
🏖️

Beach Days

Eagle Beach, Palm Beach, Baby Beach — sinking our toes into Aruba’s famous white sand and watching the waves roll in. Our happy place.

🤿

Snorkeling

Crystal-clear waters revealing colorful tropical fish, vibrant coral reefs, and even shipwrecks. Unforgettable family moments beneath the surface.

🏊

Water Sports

From jet skiing to paddleboarding, Aruba’s warm waters are our playground. The constant trade winds make it world-class for windsurfing too.

🍵

Island Dining

Fresh seafood at sunset, local Aruban dishes, and incredible restaurants — from casual beach shacks to elegant dining. Every meal is a celebration.

```

“We don’t remember days, we remember moments.”

The Waters Family • Aruba • 2012 — 2024 & Beyond
